      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Interestingly, this is the major way instanceof differs from a typecast. When v is null, <code>v instanceof C</code> is false, while <code>(C)v</code> throws a <code>ClassCastException</code>. <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jvms/se19/html/jvms-6.html#jvms-6.5.checkcast\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jvms/se19/html/&hellip;</a>"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 69443,
      "reputation" : 86825,
      "user_id" : 202009,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 79,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/31dcfef154edd75223ae28f2cfd77f71?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Andy Thomas",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/202009/andy-thomas"
    },
