      "comment_id" : 99793504,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@KaiWang The <code>instanceof</code> operator checks if a value is an instance of a certain type, <b>not if a value is assignable as (castable to) a certain type</b>. <code>null</code> is not an instance of any type, but it can still be assigned to a variable of any type. This is why <code>instanceof</code> always returns <code>false</code> for <code>null</code>, but any reference variable of an object type can hold a value of <code>null</code>."
